qQmQkv9x-7Ybksv4SsqRO-2xfcLX_INQhrvJT5shhXmBck65oXycmUVoAVoHiq8Yc9orcgnAyLOvwZ3HsT_QiOuhD9cFSKmNCAvOwjHWRLUXEIA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Gradle resource handling**\\n\\nI’m dealing with untracked files and thinking about how to inspect untracked metadata. Before committing, I should check if the build.gradle needs to include hidden resources like `.keep`. It seems Gradle processes include all files, but I wonder if it'll ignore dotfiles? It looks like `.keep` isn’t excluded. I might need to add a non-hidden file instead. There's a potential issue with naming, like using `mysql-connector-java-test` with `.keep`, which could cause loading errors.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing build environment for resources**\\n\\nI'm figuring out how the test JAR builds, which includes resources and classpath entries under `build/libs`. The JDBC isn't in the file system; instead, it's contained within the JAR. The `createMysql` function uses the path to the JAR's parent directory, so the resource won't help. I need to know the native image classpath. It looks like the test JAR is part of the `nativeTestCompile`, but I wonder if I should add a Gradle task to create paths for the JDBC before compilation. I'm also considering the impact of image initialization at runtime or build time on resources.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring setup for JDBC directory**\\n\\nI'm considering using a static initializer in the test class to set the `java.class.path` and create a JDBC directory before the `AbstractDataSourceProvider` initializes. But I realize that the native image may not execute the static initializer unless the class is initialized at build time. The class analyzer likely won't initialize the test class, so I can't just annotate it. Maybe the simplest solution is to avoid importing or extending `AbstractDataSourceProvider` in a nested class and instead use a public API to instantiate a real subclass.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_810LjwqVnWHLIikohCV6vaKD|fc_0c8ff4cfc39cb1850169f16bb4494c81969e6041d6cc241536", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/seata-all-2.1.0/reflection-calls.json", "limit": 80}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/seata-all-2.1.0/reflection-calls.json\",\"limit\":80}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1040, "output": 795, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33067, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777429414437, "responseId": "resp_0c8ff4cfc39cb1850169f16ba72a208196a6ec2510de6db8f4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_810LjwqVnWHLIikohCV6vaKD|fc_0c8ff4cfc39cb1850169f16bb4494c81969e6041d6cc241536", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"java.io.ObjectInputStream#readObject()\": [\n    \"org.apache.seata.saga.engine.serializer.impl.ExceptionSerializer.deserializeByObjectInputStream(ExceptionSerializer.java:71)\"\n  ],\n  \"java.io.ObjectOutputStream#writeObject(java.lang.Object)\": [\n    \"org.apache.seata.saga.engine.serializer.impl.ExceptionSerializer.serializeByObjectOutput(ExceptionSerializer.java:44)\"\n  ],\n  \"java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)\": [\n    \"org.apache.seata.common.loader.EnhancedServiceLoader$InnerEnhancedServiceLoader.getCompatibleService(EnhancedServiceLoader.java:562)\",\n    \"org.apache.seata.rm.datasource.util.JdbcUtils.loadDriver(JdbcUtils.java:117)\",\n    \"org.apache.seata.integration.tx.api.remoting.parser.HSFRemotingParser.getServiceDesc(HSFRemotingParser.java:102)\",\n    \"org.apache.seata.rm.datasource.util.XAUtils.createXAConnection(XAUtils.java:84)\",\n    \"org.apache.seata.saga.engine.expression.exception.Excep